Notes:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This has only been tested using:
* Gentoo Linux (2011, 2012) Stable and Unmasked
* Ubuntu Linux (10, 11, 12) Stable and Beta

Dependencies:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Apache 2+
  Modules: htaccess, mod_headers, mod_expires, mod_rewrite, mod_deflate, mod_php5, mod_mime

* PHP 5.3 +
  Modules: apache2 curl curlwrappers gd inifile mysql snmp sockets xmlreader xmlwriter zip pdo imap mhash mysqli gettext

* MySQL 5+
  Modules. UTF-8

* 'msgfmt'
  Included in Linux

* 'exiftool'
  Debian users: apt-get install exiftool
  Gentoo users: emerge exiftool
  Download: http://www.sno.phy.queensu.ca/~phil/exiftool/

* 'pdf2svg' (Optional)
  Debian users: apt-get install pdf2svg
  Gentoo users: emerge pdf2svg
  Download: http://www.cityinthesky.co.uk/opensource/pdf2svg

Installation:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
First clone the GitHub repository then set up using these instructions:

- Initialize:
* Set (temporary) permissions with './bin/fix-permissions dev' [See note]
* Create documentation with './bin/update-documentation' (Optional)

- MySQL
* Use the './schema.sql' dump.
* Edit or use connection settings in './header.php'

- Apache
* Use a vhost template in './doc/' and set up your web server
* Create /var/cache/OSjs with permission to Apache
* Update "php.ini" for the host or enable runtime ini_set for project
  The settings are found in the top of 'header.php'

- Misc
* Compile server-side locales with './bin/update-locale'
* Copy a X11's icon theme 16x16 and 32x32 folders into 'public_html/img/icons/'
  * Ex: http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/gnome-icon-theme/

- Extras
* Clone the "OSjs-Packages" repository into 'src/packages'
  * Compile all applications with './bin/application-gen'
  * Install all applications globally with './bin/install-all'

- Finish
* If you're in a production environment or doing testing procedures run
  './bin/update-compression' to compress all scripts etc. (Optional)
* Fix permissions with './bin/fix-permissions live' [See note]

[NOTE: You may have to edit the fix-permissions script to suit your environment]

Updating codebase (Production Target):
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Run './bin/git-update'

Adding Users:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Use the 'bin/add-user' script
